cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.NA 

The paper deals with the problem of clustering high-dimensional data points into low-dimensional subspaces, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the impact of dimensionality reduction on the performance of the clustering algorithms, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper uses mathematical results to quantify the change in affinities between subspaces, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the computational cost of the algorithms, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
